<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="TSJN-01-07-02-pb-0244">[244<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=TSJN/Pages/TSJN-01-07/TSJN-01-07-02-pb-0244.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
<p style="text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">Sir</span></p>
<p style="text-align: right;">Annapolis May 11. 1784.</p>
<p>Be pleased to pay to James Madison esq. four hundred and seven dollars and one third, being the balance due to me as one of the delegates in Congress for the Commonwealth of Virginia, and you will oblige Sir Your very humble servt.,</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed"><span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">Th</span>: <span class="hi-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps;">Jefferson</span></p>
</div>
<div class="postscript">
<p>The Honble Jaquelin Ambler</p>
<p>Treasurer of Virginia</p>
</div>
</div>
